parameters:
--That night, at the border town "Annabern," within Annabern
Castle's conference room.

\n<Roselitte>"--I have drafted a simple plan for the town's
reconstruction and reinforcement. Please review it later."

\n<Castle lord>"Yes, understood. I will do my utmost to meet your
expectations, Lady Roselitte."

\n<Roselitte>"...Next, let's move on to the situation report for this
region."
\n<Castle lord>"Yes, I will report while organizing the information."

\n<Castle lord>"...Deorc instigated an uprising in the northern village
'Eibel,' and soon after, he occupied the 'fortress city of
Anatos' located to the east of the village."

\n<Castle lord>"It seems that most of the residents have fled to 'Central
City Levee' to the east of Anatos, but many refugees have
also flowed into Annabern here."

\n<Castle lord>"As a result, the regional lord who also serves as the
castellan of Levee, upon learning of the situation promptly,
called for troops from various places in the region and
requested aid from the 'Imperial Mainland' to the east."

\n<Castle lord>"Thus, they quickly established a defensive line between
Anatos and Levee to prepare for the invasion of monsters...
but that's when this incident occurred."

\n<Roselitte>"...Deorc attacked this place, Annabern to the west, instead
of Levee or the Imperial Mainland to the east."

\n<Castle lord>"Yes. This town is located to the west of Anatos and is on
the opposite side of the mainland, a remote frontier town."

\n<Castle lord>"I have reconsidered why Deorc attacked Annabern... There
seems to be no clear reason for attacking here in order to
conquer Levee or the Imperial Mainland."

\n<Roselitte>"...When I met Deorc, he didn't seem all that interested in
the Imperial Mainland."

\n<Roselitte>"It's certain that he has some sort of objective here... but
thinking about it now doesn't seem to yield any answers."

\n<Roselitte>"I will bypass Anatos and head to Levee to prepare before
launching an offensive. You will continue to oversee the
security of Annabern."

\n<Castle lord>"Yes, understood.... However, Lady Roselitte, there is one
more thing I must report."
Roselitte tilted her head to prompt further explanation.

\n<Castle lord>"Just a moment ago, I received a report from the soldiers...
It seems that Levee is now surrounded by a large horde of
monsters."
\n<Roselitte>"What did you say!? Why didn't you tell me sooner!"

\n<Castle lord>"The soldiers who went to inform Levee about this matter
have just returned. I apologize for the delayed report!"

\n<Roselitte>"...Damn it. What is Deorc thinking...? Why is he targeting
Levee now... Was Annabern not his objective...?"

\n<Roselitte>"We need to come up with a plan quickly. For now, you all
must hurry with reinforcing this town."

\n<Castle lord>"Understood.... If you are planning an expedition, I will
prepare the troops. We await your orders at any time."
\n<Lyric>"It's fine, isn't it? The conversation had just paused."
\n<Roselitte>"Stop eavesdropping as well.... So, what is it?"
